World Bank Gives Funds to East Africa Bloc to Harmonize Financial Systems

-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 
2011-02-15T05:52:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/world-bank-gives-funds-to-east-africa-bloc-to-harmonize-financial-systems.html
The  World Bank  granted the East
African Community $16 million to help harmonize financial
systems in the five-nation bloc.  The nine-year project includes developing a regional bond
market, establishing a regional stock exchange and synchronizing
financial laws, the Arusha, Tanzania-based organization said in
an e-mailed statement late yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah McGregor in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  